    {
      "name": "Download API",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Initiate Download Job",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (jsonData.jobId) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('jobId', jsonData.jobId);",
                  "    console.log('Saved jobId:', jsonData.jobId);",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has jobId', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('jobId');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status is queued or processing', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(['queued', 'processing']).to.include(jsonData.status);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"file_ids\": [10000, 20000, 30000, 40000, 50000]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/download/initiate",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "download", "initiate"]
            },
            "description": "Initiates a download job for multiple file IDs.\n\n**Challenge 2 Pattern: Polling**\n\nThis endpoint returns immediately with a jobId, allowing the client to poll for status.\n\n**Request Body:**\n```json\n{\n  \"file_ids\": [10000, 20000, 30000]\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"jobId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"status\": \"queued\",\n  \"totalFileIds\": 3\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Check Download Availability",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has file_id', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('file_id');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has available boolean', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('available');",
                  "    pm.expect(typeof jsonData.available).to.equal('boolean');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"file_id\": {{file_id}}\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/download/check",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "download", "check"]
            },
            "description": "Checks if a single file ID is available for download in S3.\n\n**Note:** Files must exist in MinIO/S3 storage for `available` to be `true`.\n\n**Request Body:**\n```json\n{\n  \"file_id\": 10000\n}\n```\n\n**Response when available:**\n```json\n{\n  \"file_id\": 10000,\n  \"available\": true,\n  \"s3Key\": \"downloads/10000.zip\",\n  \"size\": 1234567\n}\n```\n\n**Response when not available:**\n```json\n{\n  \"file_id\": 10000,\n  \"available\": false,\n  \"s3Key\": null,\n  \"size\": null\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "2b. Check Download (with Sentry Test)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"file_id\": {{file_id}}\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/download/check?sentry_test=true",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "download", "check"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "sentry_test",
                  "value": "true"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Triggers an intentional error for Sentry testing.\n\nThis endpoint will return a 500 error and log to Sentry (if configured).\n\n**Challenge 4: Observability**\nUse this to verify Sentry error tracking is working."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Start Download (Long-Running)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has status', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.expect(['completed', 'failed']).to.include(jsonData.status);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has processingTimeMs', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('processingTimeMs');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.processingTimeMs).to.be.above(0);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "console.log('Processing time:', jsonData.processingTimeMs, 'ms');",
                  "console.log('Status:', jsonData.status);",
                  "console.log('Message:', jsonData.message);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"file_id\": {{file_id}}\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/download/start",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "download", "start"]
            },
            "description": "**⚠️ LONG-RUNNING OPERATION**\n\nStarts a file download with simulated processing delay.\n\n**Processing Times:**\n- Development: 5-15 seconds\n- Production: 10-120 seconds\n\n**Challenge 2: Architecture Problem**\n\nThis demonstrates why you need proper architecture for long-running downloads:\n- Cloudflare timeout: 100 seconds\n- nginx default timeout: 60 seconds\n- This request may take up to 120 seconds!\n\n**Request Body:**\n```json\n{\n  \"file_id\": 10000\n}\n```\n\n**Response (success):**\n```json\n{\n  \"file_id\": 10000,\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"downloadUrl\": \"https://storage.example.com/downloads/10000.zip?token=...\",\n  \"size\": 1234567,\n  \"processingTimeMs\": 12500,\n  \"message\": \"Download ready after 12.5 seconds\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response (file not found):**\n```json\n{\n  \"file_id\": 10000,\n  \"status\": \"failed\",\n  \"downloadUrl\": null,\n  \"size\": null,\n  \"processingTimeMs\": 8500,\n  \"message\": \"File not found after 8.5 seconds of processing\"\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
